{"author":{"id":"458c2786e2fb21c7f2463be283bdb1d457c6c22ed9854985782318ab918e2e3f"},"ops":[{"type":2,"timestamp":1461088955,"nonce":"P6l71lPaUVPhj1zwN7HxsaVlUZI=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDE3OlJlbmFtZWRUaXRsZUV2ZW50NjMzMzQ3OTc2"},"title":"BUG: DESeq2 wrapper - all vs. all produces empty output collection","was":"BUG: DESeq2 wrapper - all vs. all produces empty output collection"},{"type":3,"timestamp":1461089038,"nonce":"ddAui4f6vwJD3oehU3ds5vEm/Y8=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDIxMjA0Njk2NA==","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/715#issuecomment-212046964"},"message":"ping @bgruening, any ideas on this one? Workarounds? Thanks.","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1461093332,"nonce":"QAsbfvZi0VpHjUoXqIY6gsVPjvY=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDIxMjA3NDQ0Ng==","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/715#issuecomment-212074446"},"message":"Trying to track down this issue, and I found a couple of odd things that may be causing this...\n1. The [`deseq_out`](https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/blob/deseq_new/tools/deseq2/deseq2.xml#L148) output data element is filtered if `many_contrasts is False`. However, [the `deseq_out` string is passed using the -o parameter to `deseq2.R`](https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/blob/deseq_new/tools/deseq2/deseq2.xml#L39). The string is used by [`deseq2.R` as the base name for the output files](https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/blob/deseq_new/tools/deseq2/deseq2.R#L349). I'm not sure what the `deseq_out` string is set to when `many_contrasts` is False, but perhaps this is causing Galaxy to fail to find the datasets. Also, in the [`discover_datasets` action](https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/blob/deseq_new/tools/deseq2/deseq2.xml#L156), perhaps using `_vs_` would be better.\n2. From the [collections documentation (in the PR on Bitbucket)](https://bitbucket.org/galaxy/galaxy-central/pull-requests/634/allow-tools-to-explicitly-produce-dataset/) I don't see how Galaxy knows the format of each dataset when specifying `discover_datasets`. Perhaps something is missing from these docs?","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1461094018,"nonce":"T22voLCJ/SUHKGTKXayWxqSQxdE=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDIxMjA3ODI0OQ==","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/715#issuecomment-212078249"},"message":"After a bit more digging, I'm now thinking that the [`discover_datasets` action](https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/blob/deseq_new/tools/deseq2/deseq2.xml#L156) is just wrong. Looking at the [`discover_datasets` documentation](https://wiki.galaxyproject.org/Admin/Tools/Multiple%20Output%20Files#Number_of_Output_datasets_cannot_be_determined_until_tool_run) I believe that a `directory`must be supplied, and a regex that provides Galaxy with a `designation`. Simply putting `vs` as a filename match won't do (according to these docs).\n\nEdit, in fact, changing the line worked:\n\n```\n\u003cdiscover_datasets pattern=\"None.(?P\u0026lt;designation\u0026gt;.+_vs_.+)\" format=\"tabular\" directory=\".\" visible=\"true\"/\u003e\n```\n\nA more robust fix, however, would be to put the files into a `result_tables` subdirectory in deseq2.R and to use the shortcut `pattern=\"__designation__\"`:\n\n```\n\u003cdiscover_datasets pattern=\"__desgination__\" format=\"tabular\" directory=\"result_tables\" visible=\"true\"/\u003e\n```","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1461094742,"nonce":"0Pxw1vs7XWTAZCW4vYSCJ2cQxPw=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDIxMjA4NTYxNQ==","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/715#issuecomment-212085615"},"message":"I'd like to propose two fixes, actually. one that can be applied to the existing toolshed version ASAP (that doesn't depend on changing `deseq2.R`) and a second that go in with the next version of deseq2 where the R script is included. I'll see about getting PR's in for both of those...","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1461100152,"nonce":"GHuMgROAZevTw/xU/XPg0WZZQjQ=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDIxMjEzMDYxOQ==","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/715#issuecomment-212130619"},"message":"OK, got the first fix in, but didn't quite get to the second. I'm not sure of the correct way to get [`deseq2.R` to output the files in an appropriate subdirectory](https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/blob/deseq_new/tools/deseq2/deseq2.R#L349), which can then be specified in [`discover_datasets` in `deseq2.xml`](https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/blob/deseq_new/tools/deseq2/deseq2.xml#L156). Thoughts or advice?","files":null}]}